<subSubSection id="C306789DFFC3FF926BB0FD22FEDCFCD8" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC3FF926BB0FD22FEDCFCD8" blockId="9.[151,1436,748,880]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">
This species was recently described from 
<collectingRegion id="49D8E5F4FFC3FF92695BFD22FD0EFCAD" box="[636,720,748,773]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ar Riyad" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Riyadh</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF9269FAFD22FCADFCAD" box="[733,883,748,773]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(Sharaf and Aldawood, 2011) and was the first record of the genus from the country. Recently, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF9269F4FCC1FC95FC80" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1840" box="[723,843,783,808]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Solenopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF9269F4FCC1FC95FC80" box="[723,843,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Solenopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the Arabian Peninsula were revised by Sharaf and Aldwood (2012). At Rawdhat Khorim this species is rare, with only a single specimen collected by a pitfall trap in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
